Sentencas: For intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs), high electrochemical catalytic activity and a suitable thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) are essential criteria.
Titulo: Ca and Fe co-doped NdBaCo2O5+δ double perovskites as high-performance cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this investigation, simultaneous Ca and Fe co-doped NdBa1-xCaxCoFeO5+delta (NBCCF, x = 0, 0.1, and 0.2) double-perovskites were prepared and investigated as SOFC cathode materials.
Titulo: Ca and Fe co-doped NdBaCo2O5+δ double perovskites as high-performance cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The introduction of Ca and Fe effectively decreased the TECs and improved the oxygen reduction activity of the cathode.
Titulo: Ca and Fe co-doped NdBaCo2O5+δ double perovskites as high-performance cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average TEC of NdBa0.9Ca0.1CoFeO5+delta (NBCCF1) at 30-850 degrees C was 19.1 x 10-6 K-1, which is decreased by 27.1 % compared to the only Fe-doped NdBaCoFeO5+delta (NBCF).
Titulo: Ca and Fe co-doped NdBaCo2O5+δ double perovskites as high-performance cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: According to the distribution of relaxation time (DRT) analysis, the rate-limiting steps of the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) include bulk diffusion and surface exchange of oxygen, and Ca doping can improve both steps.
Titulo: Ca and Fe co-doped NdBaCo2O5+δ double perovskites as high-performance cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the single cell with NBCCF1 as cathode reached 665 mW cm-2 at 750 degrees C.
Titulo: Ca and Fe co-doped NdBaCo2O5+δ double perovskites as high-performance cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance decreased from 0.0722 to 0.0482 omega cm2 at 800 degrees C. These findings indicate NBCCF1 is a viable cathode candidate for IT-SOFC.
Titulo: Ca and Fe co-doped NdBaCo2O5+δ double perovskites as high-performance cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells
